div.div:
Dotted lines represent aggregate links, or logical links - these are made up of the physical links shown as regular lines. E.g.: distro0:ae100 cosnsists of distro0:ge-1/0/0 and distro0:ge-0/0/0.
Which interface is matched with which on the other end might vary slightly, but as far as configuration goes, it shouldn't matter since LACP will figure it out.
